# =============================================================================
# .factory-manifest - File ownership declaration
#
# Declares which files belong to the engine (replaced on update) vs the project
# (created on install, never overwritten). Used by:
#   - bin/install (copy_engine, copy_project to decide what to copy/skip)
#   - meta/contribute (parse_engine_files to scope the upstream diff)
#
# Format rules:
#   - Two sections: "# engine" and "# project"
#   - The parser uses regex ^#.*"$section" to detect section headers
#   - Any # line resets in_section=false, so NO comments between a section
#     header and its entries (comments there would break the parser)
#   - A blank line also ends a section
#   - Entries are plain paths: files as-is, directories with trailing /
#   - Runtime artifacts (worktree state, lock files, databases) are never listed
#
# Engine section: scripts, docs, templates, meta tools. Replaced by --update.
# Project section: config, agents, quality rules, backlog. Never overwritten.
# =============================================================================

